Module simplifier
Package ie.gmit.dip

Interface AbstractConverter<T,​U>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - a generic input type.
    U - a generic output type.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractStringConverter, StringCaseConverter, StringColourConverter, StringSynonymConverter
    public interface AbstractConverter<T,​U>
    AbstractConverter is a simple abstract interface which defines the basis of a hierarchy of classes and functional interfaces of Converter types. These Converter types take a type T as input and return a type U as output, with only a single method, convert(), required to carry out the conversion. In this sense it can be seen as similar to other functional interfaces such as Comparable, Runnable and Comparator, which implement only a single method.
    Since:
    JavaSE-11
    Version:

    Author:
